Porno Video Palace.

682
01:01:14,213 --> 01:01:16,507
I'm calling about the ad.

683
01:01:16,590 --> 01:01:18,717
- You're over 18?
- Yes.

684
01:01:18,801 --> 01:01:22,179
- Shaved?
- Sorry?

685
01:01:22,263 --> 01:01:26,517
Are you shaved?
Fur pie doesn't sell.

686
01:01:45,327 --> 01:01:47,288
How's life, Mrs. Wells?

687
01:01:47,371 --> 01:01:49,832
When you've nothing to live for...

688
01:01:49,915 --> 01:01:52,543
Come on, life's great!

689
01:01:52,626 --> 01:01:54,253
Dream on, kid.

690
01:02:09,810 --> 01:02:11,604
Hello, Mr. Dufayel.

691
01:02:12,938 --> 01:02:16,275
Here's your order, Mr. Dufayel.

692
01:02:16,358 --> 01:02:19,528
I doubt it. I hate artichokes.

693
01:02:20,279 --> 01:02:23,741
You shouldn't. Watch this.

694
01:02:29,538 --> 01:02:31,624
Take it.

695
01:02:34,335 --> 01:02:36,128
That's better.

696
01:02:48,641 --> 01:02:50,601
Lucien, you're a wizard!

697
01:02:50,684 --> 01:02:53,270
Courtesy of Mr. Collignon.

698
01:02:55,606 --> 01:02:58,233
Mister Collignon?

699
01:02:59,652 --> 01:03:01,904
Sorry, it slipped out.

700
01:03:01,987 --> 01:03:04,156
Practice, Lucien!

701
01:03:04,823 --> 01:03:07,785
Practice! Repeat after me.

702
01:03:07,868 --> 01:03:10,037
Collignon, down the john.

703
01:03:13,123 --> 01:03:16,377
- Collignon, down the john.
- Your turn now.

704
01:03:16,460 --> 01:03:17,628
Collignon...

705
01:03:20,839 --> 01:03:23,175
Collignon, big moron!

706
01:03:23,258 --> 01:03:25,928
See? You can do it.

707
01:03:26,011 --> 01:03:28,597
Collignon, dead and gone!

708
01:03:28,681 --> 01:03:30,849
Very good!

709
01:03:32,017 --> 01:03:34,895
Collignon, big moron, down the john!

710
01:03:43,654 --> 01:03:46,156
OK! That's enough for today.

711
01:03:48,242 --> 01:03:51,161
Lucien, that's enough!

712
01:03:51,245 --> 01:03:52,997
Very good.

713
01:03:56,792 --> 01:03:58,585
I found this under your mat.

714
01:05:15,537 --> 01:05:17,122
Still no win!

715
01:05:17,748 --> 01:05:20,292
Me neither.

716
01:05:22,294 --> 01:05:24,254
May I?

717
01:05:24,338 --> 01:05:26,131
There's a little...

718
01:05:32,471 --> 01:05:35,682
You're gorgeous when you blush.

719
01:05:37,184 --> 01:05:38,977
Like a wild flower.

720
01:05:39,561 --> 01:05:42,356
It's my dyspepsia.

721
01:05:44,149 --> 01:05:46,026
Morning, all!

722
01:05:46,652 --> 01:05:48,862
Beautiful day.

723
01:06:06,839 --> 01:06:08,257
Pack of Gitanes, please.

724
01:06:08,340 --> 01:06:11,301
Bravo! Vive la France!

725
01:06:11,385 --> 01:06:13,428
You scalded me!

726
01:06:13,512 --> 01:06:17,057
Ten out of ten! Bull's-eye!

727
01:06:21,645 --> 01:06:23,856
It was Amélie, she...

728
01:06:57,264 --> 01:07:01,268
When they went up Mont Blanc...

729
01:07:01,351 --> 01:07:04,730
the silicon in her face froze up.

730
01:07:05,230 --> 01:07:08,275
Her face was a festering mass!

731
01:07:34,176 --> 01:07:38,430
Mulled wine and spice cookies.

732
01:07:40,599 --> 01:07:44,478
I was too hard on the girl with the glass.

733
01:07:44,853 --> 01:07:50,150
Tell me about that boy she saw.
Did they meet again?

734
01:07:52,611 --> 01:07:55,364
They're into different things.

735
01:07:55,447 --> 01:07:57,866
Luck is like the Tour de France.

736
01:07:57,950 --> 01:08:01,578
You wait, and it flashes past you.

737
01:08:01,662 --> 01:08:06,291
You have to catch it while you can.

738
01:08:29,982 --> 01:08:31,858
Can I help you?

739
01:08:31,942 --> 01:08:34,903
Excuse me. I found this in the street.

740
01:08:34,987 --> 01:08:37,781
Nino will be glad!

741
01:08:37,864 --> 01:08:39,658
He was so sad the other day.

742
01:08:39,741 --> 01:08:41,660
I almost prayed to St. Anthony!

743
01:08:43,078 --> 01:08:45,414
Is Nino here now?

744
01:08:45,497 --> 01:08:48,292
On Wednesdays he works at the funfair.

745
01:08:50,752 --> 01:08:52,671
How long has he had this collection?

746
01:08:52,754 --> 01:08:57,426
Since I got him the job here, last year.

747
01:08:57,509 --> 01:09:01,471
Before, he collected footprints.
He worked nights.

748
01:09:02,014 --> 01:09:07,436
In the daytime, he took pictures
of footprints in wet cement.

749
01:09:07,519 --> 01:09:09,688
He's a funny guy.

750
01:09:09,771 --> 01:09:12,024
When we met, he was a Santa Claus.

751
01:09:14,609 --> 01:09:16,903
Other things, like...

752
01:09:16,987 --> 01:09:21,366
whenever he heard a funny laugh,
he'd tape it.

753
01:09:24,870 --> 01:09:26,705
Gosh!

754
01:09:27,998 --> 01:09:30,500
Must be hard for his girlfriend.

755
01:09:30,584 --> 01:09:32,878
He never keeps them long.

756
01:09:32,961 --> 01:09:35,714
Times are hard for dreamers.

757
01:09:35,797 --> 01:09:38,550
Eva! Are those coffees coming?

758
01:09:39,259 --> 01:09:40,969
Gotta go. Thanks for the album.

759
01:09:41,053 --> 01:09:44,806
It's OK. I have time
to take it to the funfair.

760
01:09:44,890 --> 01:09:49,770
Suit yourself. The Ghost Train.
Ask for Nino Quincampoix.

761
01:10:14,044 --> 01:10:15,629
Is Nino here?

762
01:10:15,712 --> 01:10:19,132
He doesn't get in till 7:00.

763
01:10:19,216 --> 01:10:22,969
- Is there no way to see him before?
- Sure.

764
01:10:23,053 --> 01:10:24,721
20 francs.

765
01:11:35,542 --> 01:11:37,711
See you next Wednesday.

766
01:11:48,972 --> 01:11:51,349
<i>5 p.m. tomorrow, Montmartre carousel.</i>

767
01:11:51,433 --> 01:11:53,393
<i>Bring 5 francs.</i>

768
01:12:11,536 --> 01:12:13,663
Want to know about her?

769
01:12:16,082 --> 01:12:19,085
- You know her?
- You bet!

770
01:12:19,169 --> 01:12:21,963
She put us in her shirt pocket.

771
01:12:22,047 --> 01:12:23,757
Next to her breast.

772
01:12:24,799 --> 01:12:28,512
- Is she pretty?
- Not bad.

773
01:12:28,595 --> 01:12:30,639
- Beautiful.
- No. Pretty.

774
01:12:30,722 --> 01:12:33,475
- Beautiful!
- Pretty.

775
01:12:33,558 --> 01:12:36,061
- What does she want from me?
- She's broke.

776
01:12:36,144 --> 01:12:38,730
She wants a reward for the album.

777
01:12:38,813 --> 01:12:40,982
Or else she collects photos too.

778
01:12:41,066 --> 01:12:46,112
She wants to trade us
for a one-eyed man with glasses!

779
01:12:50,242 --> 01:12:51,243
No, you dope!

780
01:12:52,452 --> 01:12:54,871
She's in love.

781
01:12:54,955 --> 01:12:57,916
- I don't even know her.
- You do.

782
01:12:58,917 --> 01:13:01,586
- Since when?
- Since always.

783
01:13:01,670 --> 01:13:04,047
In your dreams.

784
01:13:18,270 --> 01:13:22,816
You! Man with the plastic bag!
It's for you.

785
01:13:33,034 --> 01:13:35,537
Follow the blue arrows, Mr. Quincampoix.

786
01:15:01,456 --> 01:15:04,542
The fool looks at a finger
that points at the sky...

787
01:16:19,117 --> 01:16:21,453
I know the stranger in the pictures.

788
01:16:21,536 --> 01:16:25,540
He's a ghost. He's invisible!

789
01:16:25,623 --> 01:16:29,002
He only appears
when the film is developed.

790
01:16:30,170 --> 01:16:32,422
When a girl has her photo taken...

791
01:16:32,505 --> 01:16:35,675
he goes "wooo" in her ear...

792
01:16:35,759 --> 01:16:38,428
while he fondles her neck.

793
01:16:38,511 --> 01:16:41,097
That's how he got caught, Mr. Quincampoix!

794
01:16:44,684 --> 01:16:46,060
Who are you?

795
01:16:46,144 --> 01:16:48,313
Page 51.

796
01:16:56,237 --> 01:16:57,864
DO YOU

797
01:16:57,989 --> 01:16:59,824
WANT

798
01:16:59,908 --> 01:17:02,160
TO MEET ME?

799
01:18:40,967 --> 01:18:42,010
Listen to this.

800
01:18:42,093 --> 01:18:44,137
Boy of 6, while parents sleep...

801
01:18:44,220 --> 01:18:46,973
drives off in a pedal car.

802
01:18:47,599 --> 01:18:50,727
Found on a highway in Germany...

803
01:18:50,810 --> 01:18:54,355
he told police
he wanted to see the stars.

804
01:18:54,439 --> 01:18:58,067
Ain't life beautiful though?

805
01:18:58,151 --> 01:19:02,697
Love. The only bug she hadn't caught.

806
01:19:02,780 --> 01:19:05,700
- Nobody's immune.
- It gives me a break.

807
01:19:05,783 --> 01:19:08,077
Love's a great beautician.

808
01:19:10,246 --> 01:19:14,709
What's she like?
Tall, small? Fair, dark?

809
01:19:14,792 --> 01:19:18,504
Let's say average height.

810
01:19:19,547 --> 01:19:23,593
Not a dwarf or a giraffe. Normal.

811
01:19:23,676 --> 01:19:26,054
Pretty, for her type.

812
01:19:26,137 --> 01:19:30,850
As for fair or dark, it's hard to say.

813
01:19:30,934 --> 01:19:33,227
She wasn't a redhead.

814
01:19:33,311 --> 01:19:36,272
- Unless...
- Forget it.

815
01:19:36,356 --> 01:19:40,902
I remember she casually asked
about your girlfriend.

816
01:19:40,985 --> 01:19:42,111
And?

817
01:19:42,195 --> 01:19:46,032
I said you weren't interested, right?

818
01:19:46,115 --> 01:19:47,617
You didn't!

819
01:19:47,700 --> 01:19:50,453
What do you care?
You don't even know her.

820
01:19:50,912 --> 01:19:55,124
- Exactly. It's the mystery.
- You won't find mystery here.

821
01:19:55,208 --> 01:19:57,293
A pound of nectarines.

822
01:19:57,377 --> 01:20:00,254
The ones here are the prettiest.

823
01:20:00,338 --> 01:20:02,340
Trust him. He's an artist.

824
01:20:02,840 --> 01:20:05,468
He goes home with a ton of unsold stock.

825
01:20:05,551 --> 01:20:08,554
What for? Is he stewing a pig?

826
01:20:08,638 --> 01:20:11,015
No, sir! He's studying art!

827
01:20:11,099 --> 01:20:14,477
Sells leeks all day long
and paints turnips all night!

828
01:20:14,560 --> 01:20:16,813
The boy's a useless vegetable!

829
01:20:16,896 --> 01:20:18,398
<i>With a prompter...</i>

830
01:20:18,481 --> 01:20:22,110
<i>in each cellar window
whispering comebacks...</i>

831
01:20:22,193 --> 01:20:24,779
<i>shy people would have the last laugh.</i>

832
01:20:24,862 --> 01:20:27,907
At least you'll never be a vegetable!

833
01:20:27,991 --> 01:20:31,077
Even artichokes have hearts.

834
01:20:33,413 --> 01:20:37,208
You'll never be a vegetable.
Even artichokes have hearts!

835
01:21:37,810 --> 01:21:42,190
<i>Darling Mado, I miss you
more and more each day.</i>

836
01:21:42,273 --> 01:21:45,526
<i>I'm an exile in a world of dreary khaki.</i>

837
01:21:45,610 --> 01:21:47,528
<i>I can't sleep, can't eat...</i>

838
01:21:47,612 --> 01:21:50,615
<i>This camp was the mistake of my life...</i>

839
01:21:50,698 --> 01:21:54,535
<i>depriving me of my beloved
for five long weeks.</i>

840
01:21:54,619 --> 01:21:57,872
<i>I think of you endlessly.
Your Adrien.</i>

841
01:21:58,956 --> 01:22:04,253
<i>I turned down my last month's wages
instead of giving notice.</i>

842
01:22:04,837 --> 01:22:08,382
<i>I dream of better times ahead.</i>

843
01:22:08,466 --> 01:22:12,261
<i>An orange-colored day.
Remember, my love?</i>

844
01:22:12,345 --> 01:22:14,472
<i>Your everloving Adrien.</i>

845
01:22:15,807 --> 01:22:17,600
<i>Good news, sweetheart.</i>

846
01:22:17,683 --> 01:22:21,104
<i>Soon I'll be able to afford a car...</i>

847
01:22:21,187 --> 01:22:23,689
<i>and drive home every night.</i>

848
01:22:23,773 --> 01:22:28,694
<i>Till then, meet me on Friday,
and we'll go out.</i>

849
01:25:15,069 --> 01:25:17,280
MOTHER

850
01:25:20,199 --> 01:25:22,451
Psychiatric Helpline.

851
01:25:54,567 --> 01:25:57,028
WHERE & WHEN?

852
01:26:06,746 --> 01:26:09,081
<i>One hour later, on Boulevard St. Martin...</i>

853
01:26:09,165 --> 01:26:13,878
<i>Amélie walks into a party goods
and costume shop.</i>

854
01:26:13,961 --> 01:26:18,382
<i>At the same time, a man leaves
his home on Rue Lecourbe.</i>

855
01:26:20,634 --> 01:26:24,096
<i>26 minutes later,
Amélie is at East Station.</i>

856
01:26:28,392 --> 01:26:32,438
<i>Simultaneously, the man
in red shoes parks outside.</i>

857
01:26:32,521 --> 01:26:36,901
<i>The time is exactly 11:40.</i>

858
01:27:21,570 --> 01:27:23,531
<i>At this precise moment...</i>

859
01:27:23,614 --> 01:27:29,036
<i>only Amélie has the key
to the riddle of the mystery man.</i>

860
01:27:33,040 --> 01:27:34,875
How's it going, Mrs. Wells?

861
01:27:34,959 --> 01:27:37,878
Not so bad when it's not raining.

862
01:27:37,962 --> 01:27:41,090
- This is for you.
- Me?

863
01:27:50,266 --> 01:27:53,936
<i>Dear Mrs. Wells,
we recently recovered a mailbag...</i>

864
01:27:54,019 --> 01:27:56,188
<i>that was lost in a plane crash...</i>

865
01:27:56,272 --> 01:27:59,775
<i>on October 12th, 1969, on Mont Blanc.</i>

866
01:27:59,859 --> 01:28:04,238
<i>We are forwarding
the enclosed letter to your address...</i>

867
01:28:04,321 --> 01:28:08,451
<i>with our apologies
for the uncustomary delay.</i>

868
01:28:08,534 --> 01:28:11,745
<i>Jacques Grasjeau, Customer Services.</i>

869
01:28:12,663 --> 01:28:14,957
<i>Darling Mado, I'm in exile.</i>

870
01:28:15,040 --> 01:28:16,792
<i>I can't sleep, can't eat...</i>

871
01:28:16,876 --> 01:28:18,586
<i>I think of you endlessly.</i>

872
01:28:18,669 --> 01:28:22,590
<i>I know I've made the mistake of my life.</i>

873
01:28:22,673 --> 01:28:25,259
<i>I turned down that woman's money.</i>

874
01:28:25,342 --> 01:28:30,264
<i>If all goes well,
I'll soon be able to afford a house.</i>

875
01:28:30,347 --> 01:28:33,476
<i>I dream of better times ahead...</i>

876
01:28:33,559 --> 01:28:36,270
<i>when you'll forgive me
and join me here...</i>

877
01:28:36,353 --> 01:28:38,898
<i>one orange-colored day.</i>

878
01:28:38,981 --> 01:28:41,233
<i>Your everloving Adrien.</i>

879
01:29:10,596 --> 01:29:13,224
Another package for you.

880
01:29:23,984 --> 01:29:26,070
You heard about the concierge?

881
01:29:27,154 --> 01:29:29,573
She got a letter.

882
01:29:29,657 --> 01:29:33,410
From her husband, 40 years late.

883
01:29:34,912 --> 01:29:37,456
That's a lot, isn't it?

884
01:29:50,052 --> 01:29:53,472
I'm not big on still life, Mr. Dufayel.

885
01:29:53,556 --> 01:29:56,642
Then work on your lean layer.

886
01:29:56,725 --> 01:29:59,436
Fat over lean. Always!

887
01:30:20,791 --> 01:30:24,336
I heard there'll soon be a new star.

888
01:30:24,420 --> 01:30:27,548
You're into stars now?

889
01:30:27,631 --> 01:30:31,677
I saw it on TV at my ma's, that's why.

890
01:30:33,220 --> 01:30:35,306
I dunno if it's true.

891
01:30:36,640 --> 01:30:38,142
In America...

892
01:30:38,225 --> 01:30:41,770
they'll take rich people's ashes...

893
01:30:41,854 --> 01:30:43,731
put them in a satellite...

894
01:30:43,814 --> 01:30:45,858
and shoot it into space.

895
01:30:45,941 --> 01:30:48,277
It's going to shine forever.

896
01:30:52,865 --> 01:30:54,575
And Lady Di...

897
01:30:54,658 --> 01:30:56,869
will they do the same for her?

898
01:30:56,952 --> 01:31:00,372
Lady Di! Lady Di! Give it a rest!

899
01:31:00,456 --> 01:31:02,166
I can't concentrate!

900
01:31:04,251 --> 01:31:08,130
Lady Di! Lady Di!

901
01:31:08,213 --> 01:31:10,007
Renoir!

902
01:33:15,257 --> 01:33:17,176
I don't understand.

903
01:33:18,719 --> 01:33:21,054
Brilliant! You were perfect.

904
01:33:21,138 --> 01:33:24,349
- Did it work?
- It's getting there.

905
01:33:24,433 --> 01:33:27,311
Ask me again anytime. The harm's done.

906
01:33:27,394 --> 01:33:31,023
- Harm?
- Everybody calls me Snow White!

907
01:34:37,381 --> 01:34:39,591
THE TWO WINDMILLS AT 4 P.M.

908
01:34:48,058 --> 01:34:51,895
Could you stand in for me at 4:00?

909
01:34:51,979 --> 01:34:53,730
Again?

910
01:35:02,072 --> 01:35:04,408
What's eating him?

911
01:35:04,491 --> 01:35:08,120
- I smile too much.
- He'd rather you frowned?

912
01:35:08,203 --> 01:35:10,330
With other men, yes.

913
01:35:13,750 --> 01:35:15,460
<i>Nino is late.</i>

914
01:35:15,544 --> 01:35:18,130
<i>Amélie can only see two explanations.</i>

915
01:35:18,213 --> 01:35:20,424
<i>1, he didn't get the photo.</i>

916
01:35:21,758 --> 01:35:24,761
<i>2, before he could assemble it...</i>

917
01:35:24,845 --> 01:35:29,016
<i>a gang of bank robbers took him hostage.</i>

918
01:35:29,099 --> 01:35:31,059
<i>The cops gave chase.</i>

919
01:35:31,143 --> 01:35:34,646
<i>They got away but he caused a crash.</i>

920
01:35:37,274 --> 01:35:40,193
<i>When he came to, he'd lost his memory.</i>

921
01:35:41,570 --> 01:35:43,405
<i>An ex-con picked him up...</i>

922
01:35:43,488 --> 01:35:47,868
<i>mistook him for a fugitive
and shipped him to Istanbul.</i>

923
01:35:48,660 --> 01:35:50,412
<i>There he met some Afghan raiders...</i>

924
01:35:50,495 --> 01:35:54,499
<i>who took him to steal
some Russian warheads.</i>

925
01:35:58,170 --> 01:36:01,965
<i>But their truck hit a mine in Tajikistan.</i>

926
01:36:02,049 --> 01:36:05,052
<i>He survived, took to the hills...</i>

927
01:36:05,135 --> 01:36:07,429
<i>and became a Mujaheddin.</i>

928
01:36:07,512 --> 01:36:10,557
<i>Amélie refuses to get upset for a guy...</i>

929
01:36:10,641 --> 01:36:15,145
<i>who'll eat borscht all his life
in a hat like a tea cozy.</i>

930
01:36:34,456 --> 01:36:37,417
- What can I get you?
- Coffee, please.

931
01:37:29,344 --> 01:37:31,680
TODAY'S MENU

932
01:37:40,439 --> 01:37:42,107
<i>He's understood.</i>

933
01:37:42,899 --> 01:37:45,402
<i>He's going to put down his spoon...</i>

934
01:37:46,820 --> 01:37:50,407
<i>dip his finger in the sugar...</i>

935
01:37:55,912 --> 01:37:59,958
<i>turn around slowly and speak to me.</i>

936
01:38:09,634 --> 01:38:11,136
Is this you?

937
01:38:16,641 --> 01:38:18,060
Yes, it's you.

938
01:38:43,251 --> 01:38:46,421
- More coffee?
- No thanks.

939
01:39:07,692 --> 01:39:12,322
So it's this man here, with his hand up?

940
01:39:16,743 --> 01:39:19,830
Is she in love with him?

941
01:39:25,252 --> 01:39:29,798
I think it's time she took a real risk.

942
01:39:29,881 --> 01:39:33,260
She might. She's devising a stratagem.

943
01:39:33,343 --> 01:39:37,472
She's fond of stratagems.

944
01:39:41,810 --> 01:39:44,688
In fact, she's cowardly.

945
01:39:45,147 --> 01:39:49,234
That's why I can't capture her look.

946
01:39:50,527 --> 01:39:56,032
Dufayel's attempts to meddle
are intolerable!

947
01:39:58,535 --> 01:40:04,457
If Amélie chooses to live in a dream...

948
01:40:04,541 --> 01:40:08,712
and remain an introverted young woman...

949
01:40:08,795 --> 01:40:13,425
she has an absolute right
to mess up her life!

950
01:40:48,084 --> 01:40:49,920
What are you doing?

951
01:40:52,088 --> 01:40:54,507
Tell me, Lucien.

952
01:40:54,591 --> 01:40:59,804
For deliveries, do you keep
keys to all the apartments?

953
01:41:11,858 --> 01:41:15,737
One of your booths is out of order.

954
01:41:18,406 --> 01:41:21,326
It seems to be jammed.

955
01:41:21,409 --> 01:41:23,787
East Station ticket hall.

956
01:41:26,665 --> 01:41:29,417
Buy a video, get one free?

957
01:41:38,301 --> 01:41:39,719
Samantha?

958
01:41:49,312 --> 01:41:52,524
Can you stand in for me at...

959
01:42:13,211 --> 01:42:17,799
Photo booth.
East Station. Tuesday 5 p.m.

960
01:43:31,331 --> 01:43:33,291
Almost done.

961
01:43:37,754 --> 01:43:41,966
<i>The mystery man wasn't a ghost
or a man scared of aging...</i>

962
01:43:42,050 --> 01:43:43,927
<i>but simply the repairman...</i>

963
01:43:44,010 --> 01:43:46,930
<i>a normal technician doing his work.</i>

964
01:44:35,812 --> 01:44:40,024
He keeps spying on me.
It's making me sick.

965
01:44:40,108 --> 01:44:43,862
4:05, blatant female conspiracy.

966
01:44:43,945 --> 01:44:48,116
Gosh, you're tense!

967
01:44:48,199 --> 01:44:50,160
Good luck. You'll need it.

968
01:44:56,082 --> 01:44:57,750
Excuse me.

969
01:44:58,334 --> 01:45:01,254
- Did you put this in my pocket?
- Yes, but it's not from me.

970
01:45:01,337 --> 01:45:03,256
I know. Where is she?

971
01:45:03,339 --> 01:45:05,008
She's at her father's.

972
01:45:05,675 --> 01:45:07,677
It bothers me. Can I talk to you?

973
01:45:08,845 --> 01:45:10,472
I get off at 6:00.

974
01:45:10,555 --> 01:45:12,807
- Can you come back?
- OK.

975
01:45:13,475 --> 01:45:14,642
See you then.

976
01:45:15,894 --> 01:45:18,855
4:08, docking scheduled.

977
01:45:50,094 --> 01:45:53,139
A blond guy in a camel coat.

978
01:45:53,223 --> 01:45:54,974
Absent-minded too.

979
01:45:55,058 --> 01:45:57,310
How come?

980
01:45:57,393 --> 01:46:00,063
He came back three times the same day.

981
01:46:01,064 --> 01:46:02,482
1:12.

982
01:46:02,565 --> 01:46:04,067
Camel coat.

983
01:46:04,150 --> 01:46:05,193
2:50.

984
01:46:05,276 --> 01:46:06,653
Camel coat.

985
01:46:06,736 --> 01:46:10,281
- 4:17.
- Stop it!

986
01:46:10,365 --> 01:46:13,576
My rash has come back!
Look. Suzanne!

987
01:46:13,660 --> 01:46:17,956
My rash is back.
He's driving me nuts!

988
01:46:18,039 --> 01:46:19,582
Lay off!

989
01:46:20,250 --> 01:46:22,961
Her conscience is at fault.

990
01:46:23,044 --> 01:46:25,922
I've had it! I'm going home.

991
01:46:26,756 --> 01:46:30,009
Psychos are the last straw!

992
01:46:33,721 --> 01:46:37,183
Stop smothering them.
Women need air.

993
01:46:37,267 --> 01:46:40,520
You give them air, they blow you off.

994
01:46:40,603 --> 01:46:42,438
Fresh air's healthy.

995
01:46:42,522 --> 01:46:44,357
Cram it, failure!

996
01:46:46,985 --> 01:46:48,778
Failed writer, failed life...

997
01:46:49,529 --> 01:46:51,364
I love the word fail.

998
01:46:51,447 --> 01:46:53,157
Failure is human destiny.

999
01:46:53,241 --> 01:46:54,993
It's gasbag time!

1000
01:46:55,076 --> 01:46:58,371
Failure teaches us
that life is but a draft...

1001
01:46:58,454 --> 01:47:02,834
a long rehearsal
for a show that will never play.

1002
01:47:03,751 --> 01:47:05,461
I bet he stole that.

1003
01:47:05,545 --> 01:47:08,631
I do have some original ideas...

1004
01:47:09,299 --> 01:47:12,260
but people always steal them.

1005
01:47:12,343 --> 01:47:14,095
Same as your women.

1006
01:47:14,178 --> 01:47:16,180
Meaning?

1007
01:47:16,973 --> 01:47:19,434
You'd better get used to it.

1008
01:47:19,517 --> 01:47:22,353
Speak for yourself, you...

1009
01:47:26,816 --> 01:47:28,943
- What's going on?
- Nothing much.

1010
01:47:29,027 --> 01:47:31,779
Georgette went out, Joseph got mad.

1011
01:47:31,863 --> 01:47:33,323
Went out?

1012
01:47:33,406 --> 01:47:36,451
Like Gina.
You know who Gina's with?

1013
01:47:37,035 --> 01:47:39,329
The guy with the plastic bag!

1014
01:47:40,204 --> 01:47:42,832
I saw their little game.

1015
01:47:42,915 --> 01:47:45,043
The note in the coat pocket.

1016
01:47:45,126 --> 01:47:46,544
4:08.

1017
01:47:46,628 --> 01:47:50,715
Back he comes, and hey presto!
Out they go.

1018
01:47:54,677 --> 01:47:57,847
I'm worried for Amélie because I like you.

1019
01:47:57,930 --> 01:47:59,223
What do you mean?

1020
01:47:59,307 --> 01:48:02,935
By and large,
the men I like are mentally unsound.

1021
01:48:03,019 --> 01:48:05,063
I'd like to know more about you.

1022
01:48:05,146 --> 01:48:06,272
Ask me.

1023
01:48:08,900 --> 01:48:11,778
One swallow doesn't make?

1024
01:48:11,861 --> 01:48:13,446
A swallow?

1025
01:48:14,447 --> 01:48:15,990
A summer.

1026
01:48:16,074 --> 01:48:17,450
Practice makes...

1027
01:48:17,533 --> 01:48:18,951
Perfect.

1028
01:48:19,035 --> 01:48:20,536
- Curiosity...
- Killed the cat.

1029
01:48:20,620 --> 01:48:22,080
- Haste...
- Makes waste.

1030
01:48:22,163 --> 01:48:23,956
- Rolling stone...
- Gathers no moss.

1031
01:48:24,040 --> 01:48:26,084
- It's a sin...
- To steal a pin.

1032
01:48:26,167 --> 01:48:29,754
- Absence makes...
- The heart grow fonder.

1033
01:48:29,837 --> 01:48:31,839
- Not bad.
- You collect them?

1034
01:48:31,923 --> 01:48:36,803
At home, we say a man
who knows proverbs can't be all bad.

1035
01:48:40,640 --> 01:48:44,143
Pretty girl from the fifth floor,
listen to this!

1036
01:48:44,227 --> 01:48:48,523
- You believe in miracles?
- Not today.

1037
01:48:48,606 --> 01:48:50,858
You're in for a surprise.

1038
01:48:50,942 --> 01:48:54,487
What if I told you
that a team of climbers...

1039
01:48:54,570 --> 01:48:58,241
on Mont Blanc had found...

1040
01:48:58,324 --> 01:49:03,329
hard proof that my husband loved me?

1041
01:49:35,903 --> 01:49:38,239
Lucien, I need some yeast.

1042
01:49:38,322 --> 01:49:40,158
For Miss Amélie?

1043
01:49:40,241 --> 01:49:42,201
She's baking her famous plum cake?

1044
01:49:42,285 --> 01:49:44,370
Collignon! Go!

1045
01:49:44,454 --> 01:49:46,289
I'll be right back.

1046
01:51:12,750 --> 01:51:15,169
I'LL BE BACK.

1047
01:51:44,407 --> 01:51:47,535
Go into the bedroom, Miss Poulain.

1048
01:52:03,509 --> 01:52:07,763
So, little Amélie...

1049
01:52:07,847 --> 01:52:10,808
your bones aren't made of glass.

1050
01:52:10,892 --> 01:52:14,103
You can take life's knocks.

1051
01:52:14,186 --> 01:52:18,566
If you let this chance go by...

1052
01:52:19,609 --> 01:52:24,655
eventually, your heart will become...

1053
01:52:24,739 --> 01:52:30,453
as dry and brittle as my skeleton.

1054
01:52:32,830 --> 01:52:34,498
So...

1055
01:52:34,582 --> 01:52:38,294
go get him, for Pete's sake!

1056
01:55:25,336 --> 01:55:27,963
Without you, today's emotions...

1057
01:55:28,047 --> 01:55:31,425
would be the scurf of yesterday's.

1058
01:56:27,565 --> 01:56:29,066
International airport.

1059
01:56:29,150 --> 01:56:34,280
<i>September 28, 1997.
It is exactly 11 a.m.</i>

1060
01:56:34,363 --> 01:56:37,116
<i>At the funfair, near the ghost train...</i>

1061
01:56:37,199 --> 01:56:40,119
<i>the marshmallow twister's twisting...</i>

1062
01:56:40,202 --> 01:56:43,080
<i>while in Villette Park, Félix Lerbier...</i>

1063
01:56:43,164 --> 01:56:46,041
<i>learns there are more links
in his brain...</i>

1064
01:56:46,125 --> 01:56:48,252
<i>than atoms in the universe.</i>

1065
01:56:49,545 --> 01:56:51,630
<i>At the Sacré Coeur...</i>

1066
01:56:51,714 --> 01:56:53,549
<i>the Cardinals are practicing
their backhands.</i>

1067
01:56:54,049 --> 01:56:56,302
<i>The temperature is 24 degrees Celsius.</i>

1068
01:56:56,385 --> 01:56:58,179
<i>Humidity, 70%.</i>

1069
01:56:58,262 --> 01:57:01,557
<i>Atmospheric pressure, 999 millibars.</i>
